---
title: Puglia-Style Shrimp Orecchiette with Roasted Tomato, Parmesan & Parsley
description: This simple, rustic pasta dish will take you straight to the heel of Italy’s boot–the Puglia region, where this dish is from. It stars burst tomatoes roasted with garlic and panko and a glossy olive-oil rich sauce. You’ll garnish it generously with Parmesan and parsley and there it is–an authentic Italian dinner in a quick 20 minutes–delizioso!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/664362e638584bf020f8c6b1-78efb006.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6644f622f8c6b653637e5b0f-en-US.pdf
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/puglia-style-shrimp-orecchiette-6644f622f8c6b653637e5b0f
servings: 2
time required: 20 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 860 kcal
  fat: 40 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 82 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 40 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1050 mg
cuisine: Southern Europe
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and finely dice @onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped).

Toss @grape tomatoes{8%ounce}, onion, garlic, and @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} on a #baking sheet with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon}, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until tomatoes burst, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels. Season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add shrimp; cook, stirring frequently, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @orecchiette pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain.

Return drained orecchiette to pot. Drizzle with @olive oil{3%tablespoon}.

Add roasted tomato mixture to pot with pasta; stir to combine, adding more olive oil a drizzle at a time if needed, until everything is coated in a glossy sauce. (TIP: Stir pasta vigorously to prevent it from sticking together.) Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Stir shrimp into pasta along with roasted tomato mixture.

Divide pasta between #shallow bowls{}. Garnish with @Parmesan cheese{6%tablespoon} and parsley. Serve.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.